description.p:
This object can be obtained by providing a method of printing for improving ink absorption into a printed print substrate by preventing evaporation, the method comprising the steps of:


a. applying a layer of a pre-treatment liquid to a surface of a print substrate

b. printing an image on top of the layer of the pre-treatment liquid;

c. pre-drying a printed print substrate obtained in step b at a temperature of between 30 and 50 degrees Celsius for 2-6 seconds;

d. drying of and/or fixation of the image on the print printed substrate obtained in step c

In another aspect the present invention pertains to a printing system for performing the method according to the present invention, the printing system comprising:


a pre-treatment application module;

an image formation module (1);

a drying/fixation module (20); and

a pre-drying module (10)arranged between the image formation module (1) and the drying/fixation module (20) In an embodiment, the pre-drying module (10) comprises a heater (12) arranged for heating a printed print substrate to a temperature of between 30 and 50 degrees Celsius for 2-6 seconds,

claim.claim-text:
Method of printing for improving print quality, the method comprising the steps of:
a. applying a layer of a pre-treatment liquid to a surface of a print substrate
b. printing an image with one or more ink compositions on top of the layer of the pre-treatment liquid;
c. pre-drying a printed print substrate obtained in step b at a temperature of between 30 and 50 degrees Celsius for 2-6 seconds;
d. drying of and/or fixation of the image on the print printed substrate obtained in step c

A printing system for performing the method of claim 1, the printing system comprising:
- a pre-treatment application module;
- an image formation module (1);
- a drying/fixation module (20); and
- a pre-drying module (10) arranged between the image formation module (1) and the drying/fixation module (20).
